<p>Production break after Job (ends with a shorter than normal quire of four leaves); psalms are missing; Proverbs starts on a new quire. Ends with a shorter than normal quire, but a rubric implies that more material was expected to be added, possibly the New Testament. Missing two quires at the beginning may have contained the General Prologue. Three quires missing between the quires 18 and 23 may have contained psalms, though there is a catchword in red, probably in the hand of the original rubricator, joining the end of Job and Proverbs.</p>
